<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5162] CLOB INOUT arg set to NULL by procedure does not preserve NULL value when re-invoked</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5162</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a procedure sets an INOUT CLOB arg to NULL and is then re-invoked, the NULL is not preserved. Instead, the procedure sees the same CLOB that it saw in the last invocation. This bug was disclosed during the testing of the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2515&quot; title=&quot;Network client does not retain the INOUT parameter value change for subsequent execution&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-2515&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-2515&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I will attach a repro.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
